## What This Project Is About

Retail businesses lose revenue by treating all customers the same. A loyal high-spender and a one-time buyer need completely different marketing strategies.

This project builds an **end-to-end customer segmentation pipeline** that:
1. Takes raw retail transaction data
2. Engineers RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) features per customer
3. Groups customers into meaningful segments using K-Means clustering
4. Visualizes insights in a Power BI / Looker Studio dashboard
5. Deploys a live Streamlit app where you can look up any customer's segment

**Business Question:** *"Who are our customers, and how should we engage them differently?"*

